  "local_port": 52478,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the best coffee shops with Wi-Fi in San Francisco for evening work?",
  "response": "San Francisco is renowned for its vibrant coffee culture, offering numerous coffee shops that provide excellent Wi-Fi, comfortable seating, and a conducive environment for evening work. Here are some of the top options to consider:\n\n1. **Blue Bottle Coffee**\n   - **Locations:** Multiple, including Ferry Building, Hayes Valley, and Mission\n   - **Highlights:** Known for its high-quality beans and minimalist aesthetic, Blue Bottle offers ample seating and reliable Wi-Fi. The Ferry Building location, in particular, provides stunning views and a lively atmosphere in the evenings.\n   - **Website:** [Blue Bottle Coffee](https://bluebottlecoffee.com/)\n\n2. **Sightglass Coffee**\n   - **Locations:** SoMa, Mission, and other neighborhoods\n   - **Highlights:** A local favorite with spacious interiors, Sightglass offers a comfortable environment for working. Their large communal tables and excellent coffee make it a great spot for productivity.\n   - **Website:** [Sightglass Coffee](https://sightglasscoffee.com/)\n\n3. **The Mill**\n   - **Location:** 736 Divisadero St, NoPa\n   - **Highlights:** A blend of bakery and coffee shop, The Mill is perfect for those who enjoy fresh pastries alongside their coffee. The cozy ambiance and dependable Wi-Fi make it ideal for evening work sessions.\n   - **Website:** [The Mill](https://themillsf.com/)\n\n4. **Philz Coffee**\n   - **Locations:** Various, including the Mission District and Hayes Valley\n   - **Highlights:** Famous for its customized coffee blends, Philz provides a relaxed atmosphere with plenty of seating. Some locations have extended evening hours, making them suitable for night owls.\n   - **Website:** [Philz Coffee](https://philzcoffee.com/)\n\n5. **Ritual Coffee Roasters**\n   - **Locations:** Mission District and other areas\n   - **Highlights:** Ritual offers a hip environment with strong coffee and reliable internet. The Mission location is particularly bustling in the evenings, providing a dynamic space for work.\n   - **Website:** [Ritual Coffee Roasters](https://www.ritualcoffee.com/)\n\n6. **Four Barrel Coffee**\n   - **Location:** 375 Valencia St, Mission District\n   - **Highlights:** With a rustic interior and organic coffee options, Four Barrel is a great place to focus on your work. The Mission location is spacious and often less crowded in the evenings.\n   - **Website:** [Four Barrel Coffee](https://fourbarrelcoffee.com/)\n\n7. **Cafe R\u00e9veille**\n   - **Locations:** Mission Bay, North Beach, and other neighborhoods\n   - **Highlights:** Offering a diverse menu beyond just coffee, Cafe R\u00e9veille provides a comfortable setting with good Wi-Fi. Their multiple locations make it easy to find a spot that's convenient for you.\n   - **Website:** [Cafe R\u00e9veille](https://caffereveille.com/)\n\n8. **Peet\u2019s Coffee**\n   - **Locations:** Numerous across the city, including the Financial District and Union Square\n   - **Highlights:** A reliable chain with consistent Wi-Fi and comfortable seating. Peet\u2019s is a dependable choice for evening work, especially in central locations.\n   - **Website:** [Peet\u2019s Coffee](https://www.peets.com/)\n\n9. **Equator Coffees & Teas**\n   - **Locations:** Inner Richmond, Downtown, and other areas\n   - **Highlights:** Known for sustainable practices and quality beverages, Equator offers a serene environment perfect for focused work. Their spacious locations typically have plenty of outlets and reliable internet.\n   - **Website:** [Equator Coffees](https://www.equatorcoffees.com/)\n\n10. **Latte Art Shop**\n    - **Location:** 1255 Mission St, SoMa\n    - **Highlights:** A cozy spot with a focus on quality espresso and latte art. The warm ambiance and dependable Wi-Fi make it a pleasant place to work into the evening.\n    - **Note:** It's always a good idea to check the current operating hours, as some coffee shops may adjust their schedules.\n\n**Tips for Evening Work at Coffee Shops:**\n- **Check Operating Hours:** Ensure the coffee shop is open during the hours you plan to work.\n- **Consider Noise Levels:** Some places may become busier and noisier in the evenings. If you prefer a quieter environment, look for spots known for a more relaxed atmosphere.\n- **Power Outlets:** If you need to charge your devices, prioritize locations that offer ample power outlets.\n- **Reservations:** Though not common for most coffee shops, some popular spots might have limited seating during peak hours. Arriving early or during off-peak times can help secure a good spot.\n\nHappy working!",
